---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 143
By: Sri Ramakrishna
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=Detachment From Place and
    Conditions
Glossary:
  - Person: Janaka
    Description: the Father of Sîtâ. was a great philosopher king, of whom we
      have a similar prototype in Solomon.
    Life: 7th century BCE
---
A householder, endowed with knowledge like Janaka’s, can enjoy fruit both
from the tree and from the ground. He can serve holy men, entertain guests,
and do other things like that. I said to the Divine Mother, ‘O Mother, I
don’t want to be a dry sâdhu.
